1
00:00:22,523 --> 00:00:23,649
Sorry.

2
00:01:01,144 --> 00:01:03,146
(WHIRRING)

3
00:01:04,648 --> 00:01:06,483
(SCREAMING)

4
00:01:15,492 --> 00:01:17,327
WOMAN: Where did she go?

5
00:01:21,790 --> 00:01:24,001
-What?
-What?

6
00:01:24,126 --> 00:01:25,836
-What?
-Who are you?

7
00:01:25,919 --> 00:01:27,796
-But...
-Where am I?

8
00:01:27,879 --> 00:01:30,507
-What?
-What the hell is this place?

9
00:01:30,632 --> 00:01:31,717
What?

10
00:01:32,134 --> 00:01:34,845
(DOCTOR WHO THEME)

11
00:02:11,298 --> 00:02:13,216
You can't do that, I wasn't...

12
00:02:13,342 --> 00:02:16,053
We're in flight! That is physically impossible.
How did...

13
00:02:16,136 --> 00:02:20,932
Tell me where I am.
I demand you tell me right now, where am I?

14
00:02:21,016 --> 00:02:22,934
-Inside the Tardis.
-What?

15
00:02:23,060 --> 00:02:24,394
-The Tardis.
-What?

16
00:02:24,519 --> 00:02:25,979
-The Tardis!
-The what?

17
00:02:26,063 --> 00:02:29,441
-It's called the Tardis.
-That's not even a proper word!

18
00:02:29,566 --> 00:02:32,194
-You're just saying things.
-How did you get in here?

19
00:02:32,277 --> 00:02:35,238
Well, obviously, when you kidnapped me.

20
00:02:35,322 --> 00:02:38,241
Who was it? Who's paying you? Was it Nerys?

21
00:02:38,325 --> 00:02:41,745
Oh, my God, she's finally got me back.

22
00:02:41,828 --> 00:02:45,499
-This has got Nerys written all over it.
-Who the hell is Nerys?

23
00:02:45,582 --> 00:02:48,335
-Your best friend.
-Hold on, wait a minute.

24
00:02:48,418 --> 00:02:51,046
-What are you dressed like that for?
-I'm going ten-pin bowling.

25
00:02:51,129 --> 00:02:53,757
Why do you think, dumbo?

26
00:02:53,840 --> 00:02:57,052
I was halfway up the aisle!
I've waited all my life for this.

27
00:02:57,135 --> 00:03:01,431
I was just seconds away and then you,
I don't know, you drugged me or something.

28
00:03:01,515 --> 00:03:03,934
-I haven't done anything.
-I'm having the police on you.

29
00:03:04,017 --> 00:03:06,061
Me and my husband,
as soon as he is my husband,

30
00:03:06,144 --> 00:03:09,272
we're gonna sue the living backside off you.

31
00:03:13,652 --> 00:03:16,196
No! Wait a minute, wait a minute, don't!

32
00:03:24,121 --> 00:03:25,789
You're in space.

33
00:03:26,957 --> 00:03:32,212
Outer space. This is my...spaceship.

34
00:03:33,046 --> 00:03:35,132
It's called the Tardis.

35
00:03:35,215 --> 00:03:38,885
-How am I breathing?
-The Tardis is protecting us.

36
00:03:41,471 --> 00:03:45,851
-Who are you?
-I'm the Doctor. You?

37
00:03:47,853 --> 00:03:49,479
Donna.

38
00:03:50,731 --> 00:03:53,483
-Human?
-Yeah.

39
00:03:53,567 --> 00:03:56,445
-Is that optional?
-Well, it is for me.

40
00:04:01,366 --> 00:04:04,619
-You're an alien?
-Yeah.

41
00:04:10,000 --> 00:04:12,294
It's freezing with these doors open.

42
00:04:14,588 --> 00:04:18,049
I don't understand it and I understand
everything. This can't happen.

43
00:04:18,175 --> 00:04:20,719
There is no way a human being
can lock itself onto the Tardis

44
00:04:20,802 --> 00:04:24,014
and transport itself inside. It must be...

45
00:04:24,097 --> 00:04:27,309
There's some sort of subatomic connection,
something like a temporal field.

46
00:04:27,392 --> 00:04:29,686
Maybe something pulling you into alignment
with the chronon shell.

47
00:04:29,770 --> 00:04:32,230
Maybe it's something macrobudding your DNA
with the interior matrix.

48
00:04:32,314 --> 00:04:33,982
Maybe a genetic...

49
00:04:35,066 --> 00:04:38,320
-What was that for?
-(SHOUTING) Get me to the church!

50
00:04:39,029 --> 00:04:42,240
Right, fine. I don't want you here anyway.
Where is this wedding?

51
00:04:42,324 --> 00:04:47,954
St Mary's, Haven Road, Chiswick, London,
England, Earth, the solar system.

52
00:04:50,874 --> 00:04:56,671
I knew it, acting all innocent.
I'm not the first, am I?

53
00:04:56,755 --> 00:04:59,549
How many women have you abducted?

54
00:05:02,677 --> 00:05:04,805
-That's my friend's.
-Where is she, then?

55
00:05:04,888 --> 00:05:08,725
-Popped out for a spacewalk?
-She's gone.

56
00:05:09,684 --> 00:05:11,353
Gone where?

57
00:05:13,563 --> 00:05:16,900
-I lost her.
-Well, you can hurry up and lose me.

58
00:05:21,738 --> 00:05:23,281
How do you mean, lost?

59
00:05:30,956 --> 00:05:33,250
Right. Chiswick.

60
00:05:34,292 --> 00:05:37,462
No, she didn't run away.

61
00:05:37,546 --> 00:05:40,465
We're not talking jitters, she literally vanished.

62
00:05:40,590 --> 00:05:43,051
Now go and check the house
and she if she's there.

63
00:05:43,134 --> 00:05:46,429
Oh, Angelica, that's not helping, is it?
Now smarten up.

64
00:05:46,513 --> 00:05:48,932
-Lance, any sign?
-I've looked all around, I can't find her.

65
00:05:49,015 --> 00:05:51,685
-Where the hell did she go?
-Showing off, that's what she is.

66
00:05:51,768 --> 00:05:53,770
-First day at school,
she was sent home for biting.

67
00:05:53,854 --> 00:05:55,480
-It's a bit more serious than that.

68
00:05:55,564 --> 00:05:59,860
-She's never disappeared before.
-She didn't disappear, it's a trick.

69
00:05:59,943 --> 00:06:03,405
It's one of her silly little look-at-me party pieces.

70
00:06:03,488 --> 00:06:06,449
-What if she's dead?
-Oh, don't say that.

71
00:06:11,037 --> 00:06:14,291
I said St Mary's. What sort of Martian are you?

72
00:06:14,374 --> 00:06:17,043
-Where's this?
-Something's wrong with her.

73
00:06:17,127 --> 00:06:20,338
It's like she's recalibrating.

74
00:06:22,799 --> 00:06:27,762
She's digesting. What is it?
What have you eaten? What's wrong?

75
00:06:30,265 --> 00:06:34,519
Donna, you've really got to think.
Is there anything that might have caused this?

76
00:06:34,603 --> 00:06:35,854
Anything you might have done?

77
00:06:35,979 --> 00:06:40,066
Any sort of alien contact? I can't let you go
wandering off. What if you're dangerous?

78
00:06:40,150 --> 00:06:43,153
I mean, have you seen lights in the sky

79
00:06:43,278 --> 00:06:46,740
or did you touch something,
like, something different?

80
00:06:46,823 --> 00:06:50,493
Something strange
or something made out of a piece of metal?

81
00:06:50,619 --> 00:06:53,872
Who are you getting married to?
Sure he's human?

82
00:06:53,997 --> 00:06:57,751
He's not a bit overweight
with a zip round his forehead, is he?

83
00:06:59,169 --> 00:07:00,337
Donna!

84
00:07:02,422 --> 00:07:05,091
-Donna.
-Leave me alone, I just want to get married.

85
00:07:05,175 --> 00:07:08,929
-Come back to the Tardis.
-No way, that box is too weird.

86
00:07:10,013 --> 00:07:13,725
-It's bigger on the inside, that's all.
-Oh, that's all?

87
00:07:15,226 --> 00:07:17,354
3:10. I'm gonna miss it.

88
00:07:17,479 --> 00:07:19,189
Why don't you phone them?
Tell them where you are.

89
00:07:19,314 --> 00:07:21,983
-How do I do that?
-Haven't you got a mobile?

90
00:07:22,108 --> 00:07:26,029
I'm in my wedding dress, it doesn't have pockets.
Who has pockets?

91
00:07:26,154 --> 00:07:28,198
Have you ever seen a bride with pockets?

92
00:07:28,281 --> 00:07:30,033
When I went to my fitting at Chez Alison,

93
00:07:30,116 --> 00:07:33,954
the one thing I forgot to say was,
"Give me pockets."

94
00:07:34,037 --> 00:07:37,123
-This man you're marrying, what's his name?
-Lance.

95
00:07:37,207 --> 00:07:38,959
-Good luck, Lance.
-0i.

96
00:07:39,042 --> 00:07:43,755
No stupid Martian is going to stop me
from getting married, to hell with you.

97
00:07:43,880 --> 00:07:46,841
I'm not... I'm not... I'm not from Mars.

98
00:07:47,884 --> 00:07:49,052
Taxi!

99
00:07:50,387 --> 00:07:53,306
-He had his light on!
-There's another one.

100
00:07:55,183 --> 00:07:56,351
Taxi.

101
00:07:57,143 --> 00:07:58,770
Oi!

102
00:08:00,438 --> 00:08:01,606
There's one.

103
00:08:07,696 --> 00:08:09,030
Oi!

104
00:08:11,032 --> 00:08:13,159
Do you have this effect on everyone?
Why aren't they stopping?

105
00:08:13,243 --> 00:08:15,078
They think I'm in fancy dress.

106
00:08:15,161 --> 00:08:18,748
-Get off the sauce, darling!
-They think I'm drunk.

107
00:08:18,873 --> 00:08:21,167
You're fooling no one, mate.

108
00:08:21,251 --> 00:08:23,086
They think I'm in drag.

109
00:08:25,255 --> 00:08:26,840
Hold on, hold on.

110
00:08:31,928 --> 00:08:34,431
St Mary's in Chiswick, just off Haven Road.

111
00:08:34,556 --> 00:08:37,809
It's an emergency.
I'm getting married, just hurry up.

112
00:08:37,934 --> 00:08:40,729
That'll cost you, sweetheart. Double rates today.

113
00:08:40,812 --> 00:08:43,648
Oh, my God! Have you got any money?

114
00:08:43,732 --> 00:08:46,317
Erm...no. Haven't you?

115
00:08:47,360 --> 00:08:48,611
Pockets?

116
00:08:49,738 --> 00:08:52,490
And that goes double for your mother!

117
00:08:54,576 --> 00:08:57,370
I'll have him. I've got his number, I'll have him.

118
00:08:57,454 --> 00:09:00,123
Talk about the Christmas spirit.

119
00:09:00,206 --> 00:09:03,543
-Is it Christmas?
-Well, duh!

120
00:09:03,626 --> 00:09:07,047
Maybe not on Mars but here it's Christmas Eve.

121
00:09:07,130 --> 00:09:10,884
Phone box! We can reverse the charges.

122
00:09:10,967 --> 00:09:13,303
How come you're getting married
on Christmas Eve?

123
00:09:13,386 --> 00:09:17,432
Can't bear it, I hate Christmas.
Honeymoon, Morocco. Sunshine, lovely.

124
00:09:20,477 --> 00:09:23,438
What's the operator? I've not done this in years.
What do you dial? 1007

125
00:09:23,521 --> 00:09:25,398
Just call direct.

126
00:09:25,482 --> 00:09:29,319
-What did you do?
-Something...Martian. Now phone, I'll get money.

127
00:09:41,998 --> 00:09:43,875
Oh, answer the phone!

128
00:09:46,336 --> 00:09:47,378
Hello?

129
00:09:47,462 --> 00:09:50,048
Oh, no! The battery's gone dead.
Has anyone got a charger?

130
00:09:50,131 --> 00:09:54,260
Did you try the hotel? Hello? Hello?

131
00:09:54,844 --> 00:09:57,138
Vicar, is your phone working? Mine's run out.

132
00:09:57,222 --> 00:10:00,266
I've got one wedding about to arrive
and another wedding refusing to leave

133
00:10:00,350 --> 00:10:02,227
so, yes, I do think it's a police matter.

134
00:10:03,186 --> 00:10:06,147
Mum, get off the phone and listen, I'm in...

135
00:10:06,815 --> 00:10:10,360
Oh, my God, I don't know where I am,
it's a street.

136
00:10:11,111 --> 00:10:14,322
And there's WHSmith. But it's definitely Earth.

137
00:10:23,873 --> 00:10:25,583
(BEEPING)

138
00:10:28,711 --> 00:10:30,964
Excuse me, I'm begging you.

139
00:10:31,047 --> 00:10:34,217
I'm getting married, I really am,
and I'm late and I just need to borrow a tenner

140
00:10:34,384 --> 00:10:37,220
and I'll pay you back, I promise,
and it's Christmas.

141
00:10:44,936 --> 00:10:46,437
DONNA: Taxi!

142
00:10:47,605 --> 00:10:49,357
I want to go to Chiswick.

143
00:10:50,233 --> 00:10:53,736
Thanks for nothing, Spaceman,
I'll see you in court.

144
00:10:57,866 --> 00:10:59,075
Donna!

145
00:11:22,307 --> 00:11:25,143
I promise you, mate,
I'll give you the rest when we get there.

146
00:11:25,226 --> 00:11:26,895
Oh, I look a mess.

147
00:11:28,104 --> 00:11:29,606
Hurry up.

148
00:11:34,819 --> 00:11:39,490
Hold on a minute, I said Chiswick.
You've missed the turning.

149
00:11:39,616 --> 00:11:45,121
Excuse me, we should have turned off back there.
We're going the wrong way.

150
00:11:57,300 --> 00:11:59,510
(HORN BLARING)

151
00:11:59,594 --> 00:12:02,889
What the hell are you doing?
I'm late for the wedding!

152
00:12:02,972 --> 00:12:05,808
My own wedding, do you get that?

153
00:12:12,523 --> 00:12:16,361
Turn around! Turn this cab around right now!

154
00:12:16,861 --> 00:12:18,655
Are you deaf or what?

155
00:12:22,867 --> 00:12:24,327
Oh, my God!

156
00:12:27,872 --> 00:12:30,833
Help me! Help me!

157
00:12:34,337 --> 00:12:38,466
Help me! Help me! Help me!

158
00:12:38,549 --> 00:12:42,011
Help me! Help me!

159
00:12:42,136 --> 00:12:44,681
Help me! Get me out. Help me!

160
00:12:45,932 --> 00:12:49,102
Help me, I'm being driven by a robot!

161
00:12:52,313 --> 00:12:53,690
Behave!

162
00:13:04,450 --> 00:13:06,452
You are kidding me.

163
00:13:28,016 --> 00:13:31,060
-Open the door!
-Do what?

164
00:13:31,144 --> 00:13:35,606
-Open the door!
-I can't, it's locked.

165
00:13:42,071 --> 00:13:46,451
-Santa's a robot.
-Donna, open the door.

166
00:13:46,576 --> 00:13:49,579
-What for?
-You've got to jump.

167
00:13:49,662 --> 00:13:53,708
I'm a blinking bit jumpy!
I'm supposed to be getting married.

168
00:14:36,376 --> 00:14:38,461
Listen to me, you've got to jump.

169
00:14:38,544 --> 00:14:41,255
I'm not jumping on a motorway.

170
00:14:41,339 --> 00:14:45,718
Whatever that thing is, it needs you
and whatever it needs you for, it's not good.

171
00:14:45,802 --> 00:14:48,971
-Now, come on.
-I'm in my wedding dress!

172
00:14:49,097 --> 00:14:51,849
Yes, you look lovely. Come on.

173
00:14:55,228 --> 00:14:56,312
Oh!

174
00:15:04,612 --> 00:15:06,239
I can't do it.

175
00:15:06,823 --> 00:15:08,491
Trust me.

176
00:15:09,242 --> 00:15:13,830
Is that what you said to her?
Your friend, the one you lost.

177
00:15:14,330 --> 00:15:17,583
-Did she trust you?
-Yes, she did.

178
00:15:18,334 --> 00:15:21,838
And she is not dead, she is so alive. Now jump!

179
00:15:43,276 --> 00:15:45,278
(DOCTOR COUGHING)

180
00:15:51,701 --> 00:15:56,164
Funny thing is, for a spaceship,
she doesn't do that much flying.

181
00:15:57,707 --> 00:16:01,210
We'd better give her a couple of hours.
You all right?

182
00:16:01,294 --> 00:16:02,837
It doesn't matter.

183
00:16:04,172 --> 00:16:07,550
-Did we miss it?
-Yeah.

184
00:16:08,885 --> 00:16:11,888
-Well, you can book another date.
-Of course we can.

185
00:16:13,097 --> 00:16:16,142
-Still got the honeymoon.
-It's just a holiday now.

186
00:16:17,810 --> 00:16:21,481
Yeah, yeah, sorry.

187
00:16:22,482 --> 00:16:26,360
-It's not your fault.
-Oh, that's a change.

188
00:16:29,947 --> 00:16:33,784
Wish you had a time machine
then we could go back and get it right.

189
00:16:35,286 --> 00:16:37,872
Yeah, yeah.

190
00:16:38,831 --> 00:16:42,793
But even if I did, I couldn't go back
on someone's personal timeline.

191
00:16:43,920 --> 00:16:45,546
Apparently.

192
00:17:01,771 --> 00:17:05,107
God, you're skinny. This wouldn't fit a rat.

193
00:17:05,233 --> 00:17:10,404
-Oh, and you'd better put this on.
-Oh, do you have to rub it in?

194
00:17:10,488 --> 00:17:14,909
Those creatures can trace you.
This is a bio-damper, it should keep you hidden.

195
00:17:15,785 --> 00:17:21,207
-With this ring, I thee bio-damp.
-For better or for worse.

196
00:17:26,546 --> 00:17:29,799
Come on then, robot Santas, what are they for?

197
00:17:29,882 --> 00:17:33,761
Oh, your basic robo-scavenger.
The Father Christmas stuff is just a disguise.

198
00:17:33,844 --> 00:17:36,889
They're trying to blend in.
I met them last Christmas.

199
00:17:36,973 --> 00:17:39,058
Why, what happened then?

200
00:17:40,142 --> 00:17:44,063
Great big spaceship hovering over London,
you didn't notice?

201
00:17:45,439 --> 00:17:47,775
I had a bit of a hangover.

202
00:17:49,527 --> 00:17:53,322
I spent Christmas day just over there,
the Powell Estate, with this...

203
00:17:54,991 --> 00:17:57,827
Family. My friend, she had this family, well...

204
00:18:02,832 --> 00:18:04,333
Still.

205
00:18:05,334 --> 00:18:06,961
Gone now.

206
00:18:09,171 --> 00:18:12,550
Your friend, who was she?

207
00:18:12,633 --> 00:18:16,679
Question is, what do camouflage
robot mercenaries want with you?

208
00:18:17,722 --> 00:18:21,309
And how did you get inside the Tardis?
I don't know.

209
00:18:21,976 --> 00:18:23,978
What's your job?

210
00:18:24,562 --> 00:18:26,397
I'm a secretary.

211
00:18:27,523 --> 00:18:31,027
Weird. I mean, you're not special,
you're not powerful,

212
00:18:31,110 --> 00:18:33,571
you're not connected, you're not clever,
you're not important.

213
00:18:33,654 --> 00:18:36,866
This friend of yours, just before she left,
did she punch you in the face?

214
00:18:36,949 --> 00:18:38,701
Stop bleeping me!

215
00:18:42,580 --> 00:18:44,582
What kind of secretary?

216
00:18:44,707 --> 00:18:48,169
I'm at HC Clements. It's where I met Lance.

217
00:18:48,252 --> 00:18:49,503
I was temping.

218
00:18:50,046 --> 00:18:52,048
I mean, it was all a bit posh really.

219
00:18:52,131 --> 00:18:55,009
I'd spent the last two years
at a double glazing firm.

220
00:18:55,092 --> 00:18:59,972
Well, I thought I'm never going to fit in here
and then he made me a cup of coffee.

221
00:19:00,056 --> 00:19:05,561
I mean, that just doesn't happen,
nobody gets the secretaries a coffee.

222
00:19:05,645 --> 00:19:09,649
And Lance, he's the head of HR.
He don't need to bother with me.

223
00:19:09,732 --> 00:19:12,068
But he was nice, he was funny.

224
00:19:12,151 --> 00:19:14,153
-She didn't know about that!
-She didn't...

225
00:19:14,236 --> 00:19:17,740
And it turns out he thought
everyone else was really snotty, too.

226
00:19:17,865 --> 00:19:21,077
That's how it started, me and him.
One cup of coffee.

227
00:19:21,202 --> 00:19:23,788
-That was it.
-When was this?

228
00:19:23,871 --> 00:19:27,583
-Six months ago.
-Bit quick to get married.

229
00:19:27,708 --> 00:19:29,669
Well, he insisted.

230
00:19:30,378 --> 00:19:32,505
Will you marry me?

231
00:19:34,465 --> 00:19:36,967
And he nagged and he nagged me.

232
00:19:37,593 --> 00:19:42,181
Oh, just think about it. We'd make a great couple
and I'll get rid of the dog.

233
00:19:42,264 --> 00:19:43,933
And we could do up that back bedroom.

234
00:19:44,392 --> 00:19:48,062
And he just wore me down
and then finally I just gave in.

235
00:19:48,437 --> 00:19:51,440
Please. Oh, please.

236
00:19:51,524 --> 00:19:54,652
Please, please, please, please, please, please.

237
00:19:54,777 --> 00:19:58,447
-What does HC Clements do?
-Oh, security systems, you know.

238
00:19:58,739 --> 00:20:01,659
Entry codes, ID cards, that sort of thing.

239
00:20:01,742 --> 00:20:05,788
-If you ask me, it's a posh name for locksmiths.
-Keys...

240
00:20:05,871 --> 00:20:10,292
Anyway, enough of my CV.
Come on, it's time to face the consequences.

241
00:20:10,376 --> 00:20:12,920
Oh, this is going to be so shaming.

242
00:20:15,214 --> 00:20:17,883
You can do the explaining, Martian boy.

243
00:20:17,967 --> 00:20:21,137
Yeah, I'm not from Mars.

244
00:20:24,473 --> 00:20:27,727
Oh, I had this great big reception all planned.

245
00:20:27,810 --> 00:20:29,645
Everyone's gonna be heartbroken.

246
00:20:30,312 --> 00:20:33,607
(MERRY CHRISTMAS EVERYBODY
BY SLADE PLAYING)

247
00:21:01,552 --> 00:21:03,429
(MUSIC STOPS)

248
00:21:04,889 --> 00:21:08,142
You had the reception without me?

249
00:21:08,225 --> 00:21:10,603
Donna, what happened to you?

250
00:21:10,686 --> 00:21:14,940
You had the reception without me?

251
00:21:16,525 --> 00:21:18,486
Hello, I'm the Doctor.

252
00:21:18,569 --> 00:21:22,865
-They had the reception without me.
-Yes, I gathered.

253
00:21:22,948 --> 00:21:26,660
-Well, it was all paid for, why not?
-Thank you, Nerys.

254
00:21:26,744 --> 00:21:29,371
Well, what were we supposed to do?

255
00:21:29,455 --> 00:21:34,794
I got your silly little message in the end.
I'm on Earth? Very funny.

256
00:21:34,877 --> 00:21:38,881
But what the hell happened? How did you do it?

257
00:21:39,924 --> 00:21:42,051
(EVERYONE TALKING AT ONCE)

258
00:21:47,932 --> 00:21:49,892
(WHIMPERING)

259
00:21:50,768 --> 00:21:53,187
-Oh.
-Oh.

260
00:22:07,910 --> 00:22:10,955
(LOVE DON'T ROAM PLAYING)

261
00:23:37,041 --> 00:23:39,793
Well, I taped the whole thing,
they've all had a look.

262
00:23:39,877 --> 00:23:44,256
They said sell it to You've Been Framed,
I said, more like the news.

263
00:23:44,340 --> 00:23:46,133
Here we are.

264
00:23:49,094 --> 00:23:50,888
Can't be, play it again.

265
00:23:51,639 --> 00:23:55,517
Clever, mind. Good trick, I'll give her that.
I was clapping.

266
00:23:58,520 --> 00:24:01,774
That looks like Huon particles.

267
00:24:01,857 --> 00:24:03,901
What's that, then?

268
00:24:03,984 --> 00:24:06,987
That's impossible, that's ancient.

269
00:24:07,071 --> 00:24:10,282
Huon energy doesn't exist any more,
not for billions of years.

270
00:24:10,366 --> 00:24:12,368
It's so old that...

271
00:24:17,581 --> 00:24:20,084
It can't be hidden by a bio-damper.

272
00:24:34,223 --> 00:24:37,476
-Donna! Donna, they've found you.
-But you said I was safe.

273
00:24:37,559 --> 00:24:40,020
The bio-damper doesn't work.
We've got to get everyone out.

274
00:24:40,104 --> 00:24:43,732
-Oh, my God, it's all my family.
-Out the back door.

275
00:24:47,403 --> 00:24:49,071
Maybe not.

276
00:24:57,496 --> 00:24:59,206
We're trapped.

277
00:25:06,255 --> 00:25:08,674
-Christmas trees.
-What about them?

278
00:25:08,757 --> 00:25:11,010
They kill. Get away from the tree.

279
00:25:11,093 --> 00:25:13,262
Get away from the Christmas trees,
everyone get away...

280
00:25:18,225 --> 00:25:20,811
Lance! Lance!

281
00:25:20,936 --> 00:25:23,147
DOCTOR: Stay away from the tree!

282
00:25:23,981 --> 00:25:25,649
Stay away from the tree.

283
00:25:25,774 --> 00:25:30,029
Oh, for God's sake, the man's an idiot.
What harm's the Christmas tree gonna...

284
00:25:30,112 --> 00:25:31,280
Oh!

285
00:25:50,883 --> 00:25:52,885
(SCREAMING)

286
00:26:30,255 --> 00:26:34,510
Oi, Santa, word of advice.

287
00:26:34,593 --> 00:26:36,845
If you're attacking a man with a
sonic screwdriver,

288
00:26:38,305 --> 00:26:41,016
don't let him near the sound system.

289
00:26:41,600 --> 00:26:44,103
(PIERCING TONE)

290
00:27:04,414 --> 00:27:08,752
-It's all right, Stan, you'll be all right.
-Michael, Connie.

291
00:27:11,213 --> 00:27:14,383
-Sanita, do something useful.
-What is it?

292
00:27:14,466 --> 00:27:16,468
-What were they?
-Just stop wittering, just help him.

293
00:27:16,552 --> 00:27:17,594
Look at that,

294
00:27:17,678 --> 00:27:22,307
remote control for the decorations,but there's a
second remote control for the robots.

295
00:27:22,391 --> 00:27:25,769
They're not scavengers any more.
I think someone's taken possession.

296
00:27:25,853 --> 00:27:28,480
Never mind all that,
you're a doctor, people have been hurt.

297
00:27:28,564 --> 00:27:32,067
No, they wanted you alive.
Look. They're not active now.

298
00:27:32,151 --> 00:27:36,655
-All the same, you could help.
-Got to think of the bigger picture.

299
00:27:36,738 --> 00:27:38,991
There's still a signal!

300
00:27:39,074 --> 00:27:43,245
Donna, who is he? Who is that man?

301
00:27:52,588 --> 00:27:54,339
(BUZZING)

302
00:27:54,423 --> 00:27:56,884
There's someone behind this,
directing the roboforms.

303
00:27:57,009 --> 00:27:58,802
But why is it me? What have I done?

304
00:27:58,927 --> 00:28:02,055
If we find the controller, we'll find that out. Oh!

305
00:28:02,723 --> 00:28:04,433
It's up there.

306
00:28:05,601 --> 00:28:07,769
Something in the sky.

307
00:28:09,354 --> 00:28:12,608
Clever, clever, clever boy.

308
00:28:14,443 --> 00:28:17,654
(SPEAKING ALIEN LANGUAGE)

309
00:28:18,363 --> 00:28:19,781
Little travelling man.

310
00:28:19,907 --> 00:28:21,366
(CACKLING)

311
00:28:21,450 --> 00:28:26,246
You shall come to me and the beautiful bride.

312
00:28:27,122 --> 00:28:30,834
Such secrets to unlock.

313
00:28:31,460 --> 00:28:33,795
I shall descend this night.

314
00:28:34,671 --> 00:28:38,800
I shall descend upon this Earth

315
00:28:38,926 --> 00:28:41,970
and shine!

316
00:28:44,848 --> 00:28:47,643
I've lost the signal.
Donna, we got to get to your office, HC Clements.

317
00:28:47,768 --> 00:28:51,813
I think that's where it all started. Lance!
Is he Lance? Lance, can you give me a lift?

318
00:28:54,733 --> 00:28:58,487
To you lot this might just be a locksmith,
but HC Clements was bought up 23 years ago

319
00:28:58,570 --> 00:29:00,155
by the Torchwood Institute.

320
00:29:00,239 --> 00:29:03,700
-Who are they?
-They were behind The Battle of Canary Wharf.

321
00:29:05,160 --> 00:29:06,995
Cyberman invasion.

322
00:29:07,704 --> 00:29:11,333
-Skies over London full of Daleks?
-I was in Spain.

323
00:29:11,458 --> 00:29:14,503
-They had Cybermen in Spain.
-Scuba diving.

324
00:29:14,628 --> 00:29:16,588
That big picture, Donna, you keep on missing it.

325
00:29:16,672 --> 00:29:19,341
Torchwood was destroyed,
but HC Clements stayed in business.

326
00:29:19,424 --> 00:29:22,427
I think someone else came in
and took over the operation.

327
00:29:22,552 --> 00:29:24,554
What do they want with me?

328
00:29:25,847 --> 00:29:29,476
Somehow you've been dosed with
Huon energy and that's a problem

329
00:29:29,559 --> 00:29:32,229
because Huon energy
hasn't existed since the Dark Times.

330
00:29:32,354 --> 00:29:36,817
The only place you find a Huon particle now
is a remnant in the heart of the Tardis.

331
00:29:36,900 --> 00:29:38,860
See, that's what happened.

332
00:29:40,279 --> 00:29:44,366
Say that's the Tardis and that's you.

333
00:29:44,449 --> 00:29:48,996
The particles inside you activated,
the two sets of particles magnetise and wap!

334
00:29:49,079 --> 00:29:51,206
You were pulled inside the Tardis.

335
00:29:51,290 --> 00:29:54,584
-I'm a pencil inside a mug?
-Yes, you are. 4H sums you up.

336
00:29:54,710 --> 00:29:56,628
Lance, what was HC Clements working on?

337
00:29:56,753 --> 00:30:00,048
Anything top secret,
special operations, do not enter?

338
00:30:00,132 --> 00:30:03,051
I don't know, I'm in charge of personnel.
I wasn't project manager.

339
00:30:03,135 --> 00:30:05,929
Why am I even explaining myself?
What the hell are we talking about?

340
00:30:06,054 --> 00:30:08,640
You make keys, that's the point.

341
00:30:08,724 --> 00:30:14,730
And look at this, we're on the third floor.
Underneath reception there's a basement, yes?

342
00:30:15,522 --> 00:30:19,818
Then how come when you look in the lift,
there's a button marked "lower basement".

343
00:30:19,901 --> 00:30:23,030
There's a whole floor
which doesn't exist on the official plan.

344
00:30:23,113 --> 00:30:26,992
-So what's down there?
-You telling me this building's got a secret floor?

345
00:30:27,075 --> 00:30:29,578
No, I'm showing you
this building's got a secret floor.

346
00:30:29,703 --> 00:30:32,080
-It needs a key.
-I don't.

347
00:30:33,749 --> 00:30:36,376
Right then, thanks, you two.
I can handle this, see you later.

348
00:30:36,460 --> 00:30:38,920
No chance, Martian.
You're the man who keeps saving my life.

349
00:30:39,004 --> 00:30:41,423
-I ain't letting you out of my sight.
-Going down.

350
00:30:41,506 --> 00:30:44,217
-Lance?
-Maybe I should go to the police.

351
00:30:44,301 --> 00:30:45,427
Inside!

352
00:30:48,930 --> 00:30:51,141
-To honour and obey.
-Tell me about it, mate.

353
00:30:51,224 --> 00:30:52,434
Oi!

354
00:30:59,316 --> 00:31:03,612
The bride approaches! She is my key.

355
00:31:10,118 --> 00:31:14,539
-Where are we? What goes on down here?
-Let's find out.

356
00:31:14,623 --> 00:31:17,084
Do you think Mr Clements knows
about this place?

357
00:31:17,167 --> 00:31:20,504
The mysterious HC Clements?
Oh, I think he's part of it.

358
00:31:21,380 --> 00:31:24,174
Oh, look, transport.

359
00:31:42,401 --> 00:31:44,820
(DONNA AND THE DOCTOR LAUGHING)

360
00:31:57,040 --> 00:32:01,002
Wait here, just need to get my bearings.
Don't do anything.

361
00:32:02,003 --> 00:32:05,674
-You better come back.
-Couldn't get rid of you if I tried.

362
00:32:15,434 --> 00:32:19,855
Donna, have you thought about this properly?

363
00:32:20,147 --> 00:32:22,816
I mean, this is serious.

364
00:32:22,899 --> 00:32:24,901
What the hell are we gonna do?

365
00:32:26,153 --> 00:32:28,363
Oh, I thought July.

366
00:33:02,689 --> 00:33:05,567
Thames flood barrier. Right on top of us.

367
00:33:05,650 --> 00:33:08,236
Torchwood snuck in
and built this place underneath.

368
00:33:08,361 --> 00:33:12,199
What, there's like a secret base
hidden underneath a major London landmark?

369
00:33:12,324 --> 00:33:15,035
I know. I know, love.

370
00:33:18,413 --> 00:33:21,583
Oh! Look at this.

371
00:33:22,417 --> 00:33:24,169
Stunning.

372
00:33:24,252 --> 00:33:28,465
-DONNA: What does it do?
-Particle extrusion. Hold on.

373
00:33:31,426 --> 00:33:33,220
Brilliant.

374
00:33:33,303 --> 00:33:36,431
They've been manufacturing Huon particles.

375
00:33:36,515 --> 00:33:40,852
Of course, my people got rid of Huons.
They unravel the atomic structure.

376
00:33:40,936 --> 00:33:45,232
Your people?
Who are they? What company do you represent?

377
00:33:45,315 --> 00:33:48,693
Oh, I'm a freelancer.
But this lot are rebuilding them.

378
00:33:48,777 --> 00:33:50,695
They've been using the river.

379
00:33:50,779 --> 00:33:54,908
Extruding them through a flat hydrogen base
so they've got the end result...

380
00:33:54,991 --> 00:33:57,702
Huon particles in liquid form.

381
00:33:57,786 --> 00:34:00,121
And that's what's inside me?

382
00:34:04,834 --> 00:34:06,294
Oh, my God!

383
00:34:08,505 --> 00:34:10,131
Genius.

384
00:34:10,215 --> 00:34:11,508
Because the particles are inert, they need

385
00:34:11,591 --> 00:34:14,886
something living to catalyse inside
and that's you.

386
00:34:15,011 --> 00:34:17,264
Saturate the body and then...

387
00:34:17,347 --> 00:34:20,892
Oh, the wedding!
Yes, you're getting married. That's it!

388
00:34:20,976 --> 00:34:23,770
Best day of your life, walking down the aisle.
Your body is a battleground!

389
00:34:23,853 --> 00:34:25,647
There's a chemical war inside.

390
00:34:25,730 --> 00:34:29,276
Adrenaline, acetylcholine.
Wham go the endorphins! Oh, you're cooking.

391
00:34:29,359 --> 00:34:32,362
You're like a walking oven. A pressure cooker,
a microwave, all churning away.

392
00:34:32,487 --> 00:34:34,864
The particles reach boiling point... Shazam!

393
00:34:36,533 --> 00:34:39,911
-What did I do this time?
-Are you enjoying this?

394
00:34:42,497 --> 00:34:47,502
All right, just tell me,
these particles, are they dangerous?

395
00:34:48,169 --> 00:34:51,006
-Am I safe?
-Yes.

396
00:34:53,300 --> 00:34:54,801
Doctor...

397
00:34:56,344 --> 00:35:01,057
if your lot got rid of Huon particles,
why did they do that?

398
00:35:02,350 --> 00:35:04,978
Because they were deadly.

399
00:35:05,061 --> 00:35:08,231
-Oh, my God.
-I'll sort it out, Donna.

400
00:35:08,356 --> 00:35:12,193
Whatever's been done to you, I'll reverse it.
I'm not about to lose someone else.

401
00:35:12,319 --> 00:35:14,362
(DOOR OPENING)

402
00:35:14,487 --> 00:35:17,532
VOICE: Oh, she's long since lost.

403
00:35:21,411 --> 00:35:25,165
I have waited so long.

404
00:35:25,248 --> 00:35:29,377
Hibernating at the edge of the universe.

405
00:35:29,502 --> 00:35:35,008
Until the secret heart
was uncovered and called out to waken me.

406
00:35:45,143 --> 00:35:47,228
Someone's been digging.

407
00:35:48,730 --> 00:35:52,067
Oh, very Torchwood. Drilled by laser.

408
00:35:52,150 --> 00:35:53,652
How far down does it go?

409
00:35:53,735 --> 00:35:59,074
Down and down.
All the way to the centre of the Earth.

410
00:35:59,157 --> 00:36:03,244
Really? Seriously, what for?

411
00:36:03,370 --> 00:36:05,288
-Dinosaurs.
-What?

412
00:36:05,413 --> 00:36:06,790
Dinosaurs?

413
00:36:06,915 --> 00:36:10,293
-What are you on about? Dinosaurs.
-That film under the Earth with dinosaurs.

414
00:36:10,418 --> 00:36:12,420
-Trying to help.
-That's not helping.

415
00:36:12,504 --> 00:36:15,715
Such a sweet couple.

416
00:36:15,799 --> 00:36:19,511
Only a madman talks to thin air.
And trust me, you don't want to make me mad.

417
00:36:19,636 --> 00:36:20,679
Where are you?

418
00:36:20,762 --> 00:36:23,056
High in the sky.

419
00:36:24,265 --> 00:36:29,104
Floating so high on Christmas night.

420
00:36:29,187 --> 00:36:32,399
DOCTOR: I didn't come all this way
to talk on the intercom.

421
00:36:32,482 --> 00:36:34,901
Come on, let's have a look at you.

422
00:36:34,984 --> 00:36:37,362
Who are you with such command?

423
00:36:37,445 --> 00:36:38,947
I'm the Doctor.

424
00:36:39,781 --> 00:36:43,368
Prepare your best medicines, doctor man,

425
00:36:43,451 --> 00:36:47,205
for you will be sick at heart.

426
00:36:48,039 --> 00:36:49,791
(HISSING)

427
00:36:55,130 --> 00:36:56,923
Racnoss.

428
00:36:57,507 --> 00:36:59,759
That's impossible. You're one of the Racnoss.

429
00:36:59,843 --> 00:37:03,513
Empress of the Racnoss.

430
00:37:10,687 --> 00:37:13,022
If you're the Empress,
where's the rest of the Racnoss?

431
00:37:13,148 --> 00:37:16,025
Or are you the only one?

432
00:37:16,151 --> 00:37:19,446
Such a sharp mind.

433
00:37:20,488 --> 00:37:22,407
That's it. The last of your kind.

434
00:37:22,490 --> 00:37:25,118
The Racnoss come from the Dark Times.
Billions of years ago. Billions.

435
00:37:25,201 --> 00:37:27,996
They were carnivores. Omnivores.
They devoured whole planets.

436
00:37:28,121 --> 00:37:32,667
Racnoss are born starving. Is that our fault?

437
00:37:32,751 --> 00:37:34,502
(HISSING)

438
00:37:34,627 --> 00:37:36,296
They eat people?

439
00:37:37,213 --> 00:37:41,092
HC Clements, did he wear those, uh,
black and white shoes?

440
00:37:41,176 --> 00:37:44,929
He did! We used to laugh.
We used to call him the fat cat in spats.

441
00:37:48,308 --> 00:37:49,684
Oh, my God!

442
00:37:50,518 --> 00:37:53,563
Aye! Christmas dinner.

443
00:37:53,688 --> 00:37:55,565
You shouldn't even exist.

444
00:37:55,648 --> 00:37:58,902
DOCTOR: Way back in history, the Fledgling
Empires went to war against the Racnoss.

445
00:37:59,027 --> 00:38:03,198
-They were wiped out.
-Except for me.

446
00:38:03,323 --> 00:38:06,451
That's what I've got inside me,
that Huon energy thing.

447
00:38:06,534 --> 00:38:10,663
Oi! Look at me, lady, I'm talking.
Where do I fit in?

448
00:38:10,747 --> 00:38:14,167
How come I get all stacked up
with these Huon particles?

449
00:38:14,250 --> 00:38:17,545
Look at me, you. Look me in the eye and tell me.

450
00:38:17,629 --> 00:38:22,217
-The bride is so feisty.
-Yes, I am.

451
00:38:22,717 --> 00:38:26,387
And I don't know what you are, you big thing.

452
00:38:26,471 --> 00:38:29,015
But a spider's just a spider.

453
00:38:29,098 --> 00:38:31,726
And an axe is an axe.

454
00:38:31,851 --> 00:38:33,812
Now, do it!

455
00:38:45,698 --> 00:38:48,910
That was a good one. Your face.

456
00:38:48,993 --> 00:38:51,871
Lance is funny.

457
00:38:51,955 --> 00:38:53,623
What?

458
00:38:53,748 --> 00:38:55,542
-I'm sorry.
-Sorry for what?

459
00:38:55,625 --> 00:39:00,296
-Lance, don't be so stupid. Get her!
-God, she's thick.

460
00:39:00,797 --> 00:39:03,633
Months I've had to put up with her. Months!

461
00:39:03,716 --> 00:39:06,553
A woman who can't even point
to Germany on a map.

462
00:39:10,807 --> 00:39:12,642
I don't understand.

463
00:39:13,268 --> 00:39:15,436
How did you meet him?

464
00:39:15,979 --> 00:39:18,940
-In the office.
-He made you coffee.

465
00:39:20,275 --> 00:39:21,359
What?

466
00:39:21,442 --> 00:39:25,029
Every day I made you coffee.

467
00:39:26,072 --> 00:39:30,118
You had to be dosed with liquid particles
over six months.

468
00:39:32,078 --> 00:39:34,247
He was poisoning me.

469
00:39:35,456 --> 00:39:39,711
It was all there in the job title.
The head of human resources.

470
00:39:39,794 --> 00:39:43,381
This time it's personnel.

471
00:39:45,008 --> 00:39:48,303
But... We were getting married.

472
00:39:48,386 --> 00:39:52,473
Well, I couldn't risk you running off.
I had to say yes.

473
00:39:52,557 --> 00:39:56,936
Then I was stuck with a woman who thinks the
height of excitement is a new flavoured Pringle.

474
00:39:57,020 --> 00:40:00,982
Oh, I had to sit there
and listen to all that yap, yap, yap.

475
00:40:01,065 --> 00:40:02,692
Ooh, Brad and Angelina!

476
00:40:02,817 --> 00:40:07,655
Is Posh pregnant? X Factor. Atkin's diet.
Feng shui. Split ends.

477
00:40:07,739 --> 00:40:09,449
Text me, text me, text me.

478
00:40:09,532 --> 00:40:13,661
Dear God, the never-ending fountain of
fat, stupid trivia.

479
00:40:15,997 --> 00:40:18,750
-I deserve a medal.
-Oh, is that what she's offered you?

480
00:40:18,833 --> 00:40:21,169
The Empress of the Racnoss.

481
00:40:21,252 --> 00:40:23,463
What are you? Her consort.

482
00:40:23,546 --> 00:40:25,715
It's better than a night with her.

483
00:40:26,341 --> 00:40:28,426
But I love you.

484
00:40:29,260 --> 00:40:31,012
That's what made it easy.

485
00:40:32,263 --> 00:40:36,017
LANCE: It's like you said, Doctor. The big picture.

486
00:40:36,142 --> 00:40:39,103
What's the point of it all
if the human race is nothing?

487
00:40:39,187 --> 00:40:41,564
That's what the Empress can give me.

488
00:40:41,648 --> 00:40:44,233
The chance to...go out there.

489
00:40:45,026 --> 00:40:47,987
To see it. The size of it all.

490
00:40:49,822 --> 00:40:53,368
I think you understand that, don't you, Doctor?

491
00:40:53,451 --> 00:40:56,829
Who is this little physician?

492
00:40:57,288 --> 00:41:01,417
-She said Martian.
-Oh, I'm sort of homeless.

493
00:41:01,542 --> 00:41:03,419
But the point is, what's down here?

494
00:41:03,503 --> 00:41:06,798
The Racnoss are extinct.
What's going to help you 4,000 miles down?

495
00:41:06,881 --> 00:41:09,050
That's just the molten core of the Earth, innit?

496
00:41:09,133 --> 00:41:12,679
-I think he wants us to talk.
-I think so, too.

497
00:41:12,762 --> 00:41:14,973
Well, tough. All we need is Donna.

498
00:41:15,056 --> 00:41:19,143
Kill this chattering little doctor man.

499
00:41:19,227 --> 00:41:21,020
-Don't you hurt him.
-No, it's all right.

500
00:41:21,104 --> 00:41:23,022
No, I won't let them.

501
00:41:24,065 --> 00:41:26,859
Ah! Now, except...

502
00:41:26,943 --> 00:41:28,569
Take aim!

503
00:41:28,653 --> 00:41:30,363
Well, I just want to point out the obvious.

504
00:41:30,446 --> 00:41:34,909
They won't hit the bride.
They're such very good shots.

505
00:41:34,993 --> 00:41:36,411
(STUTTERING)

506
00:41:36,577 --> 00:41:40,081
Just hold on. Hold on just a tick.
Just a tiny little, just a...tick.

507
00:41:40,164 --> 00:41:43,126
If you think about it,
the particles activated in Donna

508
00:41:43,209 --> 00:41:45,712
and drew her inside my spaceship.

509
00:41:45,795 --> 00:41:50,508
So reverse it, the spaceship comes to her.

510
00:41:51,259 --> 00:41:52,760
EMPRESS: Fire!

511
00:41:54,012 --> 00:41:55,888
Off we go, then.

512
00:41:58,224 --> 00:42:01,060
My key!

513
00:42:05,940 --> 00:42:08,526
Oh, do you know what you said before
about a time machine?

514
00:42:08,609 --> 00:42:12,113
Well, I lied. And now we're gonna use it.

515
00:42:12,238 --> 00:42:14,991
We need to find out what
the Empress of the Racnoss is digging up.

516
00:42:15,074 --> 00:42:18,786
If something's buried at the planet's core,
then it must've been there since the beginning.

517
00:42:18,953 --> 00:42:21,664
That's just brilliant. Motto bene!
I've always wanted to see this.

518
00:42:21,748 --> 00:42:25,001
Donna, I'm going further back
than I've ever been before.

519
00:42:29,338 --> 00:42:34,594
If a key is lost, then another must be cut.

520
00:42:35,011 --> 00:42:37,430
(YELLING)

521
00:42:49,692 --> 00:42:52,820
We've arrived. You want to see?

522
00:42:55,239 --> 00:42:56,949
I suppose.

523
00:43:00,620 --> 00:43:03,915
The scanner's a bit small. Maybe your way's best.

524
00:43:07,376 --> 00:43:09,170
Come on.

525
00:43:13,007 --> 00:43:15,259
No human's ever seen this. You'll be the first.

526
00:43:15,343 --> 00:43:17,470
All I wanna see is my bed.

527
00:43:20,306 --> 00:43:24,393
Donna Noble,
welcome to the creation of the Earth.

528
00:43:30,983 --> 00:43:34,070
We've gone back 4.6 billion years.

529
00:43:34,821 --> 00:43:38,032
There's no solar system. Not yet.

530
00:43:38,116 --> 00:43:40,243
Only dust and rocks and gas.

531
00:43:41,035 --> 00:43:44,247
That's the sun. Over there. Brand-new.

532
00:43:45,665 --> 00:43:47,708
Just beginning to burn.

533
00:43:49,669 --> 00:43:53,422
-Where's the Earth?
-All around us.

534
00:43:53,506 --> 00:43:55,299
In the dust.

535
00:44:00,304 --> 00:44:03,307
Puts the wedding in perspective.

536
00:44:03,391 --> 00:44:07,436
Lance was right. We're just tiny.

537
00:44:07,520 --> 00:44:10,815
No, but that's what you do. The human race.

538
00:44:11,732 --> 00:44:14,235
Make sense out of chaos.

539
00:44:14,360 --> 00:44:19,448
Marking it out with weddings
and Christmas and calendars.

540
00:44:21,492 --> 00:44:25,580
This whole process is beautiful.
But only if it is being observed.

541
00:44:27,582 --> 00:44:30,585
So I came out of all this.

542
00:44:30,668 --> 00:44:32,628
Isn't that brilliant?

543
00:44:38,342 --> 00:44:40,887
I think that's the Isle of Wight.

544
00:44:43,514 --> 00:44:45,600
Eventually, gravity takes hold.

545
00:44:45,683 --> 00:44:49,353
Say, one big rock, heavier than the others,
starts to pull other rocks towards it.

546
00:44:49,437 --> 00:44:53,441
All the dust and gas and elements get pulled in,
everything piling in until you get...

547
00:44:53,566 --> 00:44:55,151
The Earth.

548
00:44:55,276 --> 00:44:59,739
Now, the question is, what was that first rock?

549
00:45:01,657 --> 00:45:03,117
DONNA: Look.

550
00:45:04,952 --> 00:45:06,454
The Racnoss.

551
00:45:10,124 --> 00:45:15,630
Now I have measured the bride's catalysis,
I can force feed it.

552
00:45:16,964 --> 00:45:21,928
Drink the particles, become the key!

553
00:45:25,598 --> 00:45:28,226
Hold on, the Racnoss are hiding from the war.

554
00:45:28,309 --> 00:45:31,771
-What's it doing?
-Exactly what you said.

555
00:45:34,941 --> 00:45:39,153
Oh, they didn't just bury something
in the centre of the Earth.

556
00:45:39,946 --> 00:45:42,740
They became the centre of the Earth.

557
00:45:42,823 --> 00:45:44,659
The first rock.

558
00:45:44,742 --> 00:45:46,077
(RUMBLING)

559
00:45:46,160 --> 00:45:48,412
-What was that?
-Trouble.

560
00:45:48,829 --> 00:45:52,833
My wonderful key.

561
00:45:52,917 --> 00:45:56,170
Now, my servants, find him.

562
00:45:57,463 --> 00:45:59,465
What the hell is it doing?

563
00:45:59,548 --> 00:46:02,802
A little trick of mine. Particles pulling particles.

564
00:46:02,885 --> 00:46:05,930
Well, it works in reverse,
and they're pulling us back.

565
00:46:09,141 --> 00:46:11,727
Well, can't you stop it?
Hasn't it got a handbrake?

566
00:46:11,852 --> 00:46:15,690
Can't you reverse or warp or fade or something?

567
00:46:15,815 --> 00:46:18,192
Back-seat driver. Oh! Wait a minute.

568
00:46:19,902 --> 00:46:21,988
The extrapolator.

569
00:46:23,698 --> 00:46:26,200
It can't stop us,
but it should give us a good bump!

570
00:46:26,325 --> 00:46:29,704
EMPRESS: The bride shall join her groom.

571
00:46:29,787 --> 00:46:32,915
What a wedding there shall be.

572
00:46:33,541 --> 00:46:34,583
Now!

573
00:46:40,006 --> 00:46:43,009
We're about 200 yards to the right. Come on.

574
00:46:46,554 --> 00:46:51,058
She is close. The holy bride in white.

575
00:46:51,392 --> 00:46:53,394
Find her. Find her!

576
00:46:59,108 --> 00:47:02,403
-What do we do?
-I don't know. I'm making it up as I go along.

577
00:47:02,486 --> 00:47:06,282
-But trust me, I've got history.
-I still don't understand.

578
00:47:06,407 --> 00:47:09,327
I'm full of particles, but what for?

579
00:47:09,410 --> 00:47:13,331
There's a Racnoss web at the centre of the Earth,
but my people unravelled their power source.

580
00:47:13,414 --> 00:47:15,666
If Huon particles cease to exist,
the Racnoss will stop.

581
00:47:15,750 --> 00:47:18,961
They just stayed in hibernation
for billions of years, frozen, dead, kaput.

582
00:47:19,045 --> 00:47:21,922
So you're the new key.
Brand-new particles, living particles.

583
00:47:22,006 --> 00:47:25,426
They need you to open it
and you have never been so quiet.

584
00:47:25,509 --> 00:47:26,761
Oh!

585
00:47:36,937 --> 00:47:38,147
I hate you.

586
00:47:38,272 --> 00:47:40,566
Yeah, I think we've gone bit beyond that now,
sweetheart.

587
00:47:40,649 --> 00:47:45,613
My golden couple, together at last!

588
00:47:45,696 --> 00:47:48,866
Your awful wedded life!

589
00:47:49,283 --> 00:47:52,995
Tell me, do you want to be released?

590
00:47:53,079 --> 00:47:57,375
-BOTH: Yes.
-You're supposed to say, "I do."

591
00:47:58,292 --> 00:48:01,462
-No chance.
-Say it.

592
00:48:06,467 --> 00:48:08,969
-I do.
-I do!

593
00:48:09,845 --> 00:48:11,889
I don't.

594
00:48:11,972 --> 00:48:13,724
(LAUGHING)

595
00:48:13,808 --> 00:48:16,852
Activate the particles.

596
00:48:16,936 --> 00:48:19,397
Purge every last one!

597
00:48:22,650 --> 00:48:24,402
And release!

598
00:48:26,654 --> 00:48:29,657
The secret heart unlocks

599
00:48:29,740 --> 00:48:34,703
and they will waken from their sleep of ages.

600
00:48:34,829 --> 00:48:37,331
Who will? What's down there?

601
00:48:38,332 --> 00:48:39,875
How thick are you?

602
00:48:41,168 --> 00:48:45,548
My children, the long lost Racnoss,

603
00:48:45,673 --> 00:48:49,718
now reborn to feast on flesh.

604
00:48:51,929 --> 00:48:55,307
The web star shall come to me.

605
00:49:01,063 --> 00:49:05,693
My babies will be hungry. They need sustenance.

606
00:49:07,278 --> 00:49:09,738
Perish the web.

607
00:49:09,822 --> 00:49:12,533
Use her, not me. Use her!

608
00:49:12,616 --> 00:49:16,370
Oh, my funny little lad,

609
00:49:16,454 --> 00:49:20,749
but you were quite impolite to your lady friend.

610
00:49:20,875 --> 00:49:23,544
The Empress does not approve.

611
00:49:29,133 --> 00:49:31,719
Lance!

612
00:49:43,439 --> 00:49:44,982
It's Christmas.

613
00:49:45,733 --> 00:49:50,446
Harvest the humans. Reduce them to meat.

614
00:50:19,391 --> 00:50:22,811
EMPRESS: My children are climbing towards me

615
00:50:22,895 --> 00:50:26,106
and none shall stop them.

616
00:50:28,859 --> 00:50:33,864
So you might as well unmask,
my clever little doctor man.

617
00:50:35,574 --> 00:50:37,326
Oh, well, nice try.

618
00:50:38,619 --> 00:50:40,204
I've got you, Donna.

619
00:50:41,705 --> 00:50:44,166
-I'm gonna fall!
-You're gonna swing.

620
00:50:44,250 --> 00:50:45,626
(SCREAMING)

621
00:50:46,293 --> 00:50:47,795
I've got you.

622
00:50:50,714 --> 00:50:52,925
(CRASHING)

623
00:50:53,133 --> 00:50:54,802
(CLATTERING)

624
00:50:54,885 --> 00:50:56,595
Oh, sorry.

625
00:50:57,388 --> 00:50:59,807
Thanks for nothing.

626
00:51:01,183 --> 00:51:03,936
The doctor man amuses me.

627
00:51:04,019 --> 00:51:07,690
Empress of the Racnoss,
I give you one last chance.

628
00:51:07,773 --> 00:51:09,316
I can find you a planet.

629
00:51:09,400 --> 00:51:13,279
I can find you and your children
a place in the universe to coexist.

630
00:51:13,362 --> 00:51:16,156
Take that offer and end this now.

631
00:51:17,825 --> 00:51:20,327
These men are so funny.

632
00:51:20,828 --> 00:51:25,749
-What's your answer?
-Oh! I'm afraid I have to decline.

633
00:51:26,375 --> 00:51:28,669
Then what happens next is your own doing.

634
00:51:28,794 --> 00:51:31,880
I'll show you what happens next.

635
00:51:33,507 --> 00:51:35,426
At arms!

636
00:51:36,802 --> 00:51:38,846
Take aim!

637
00:51:40,598 --> 00:51:42,141
-And...
-Relax.

638
00:51:46,854 --> 00:51:50,774
-What did you do?
-Guess what I've got, Donna.

639
00:51:52,234 --> 00:51:54,153
Pockets.

640
00:51:54,236 --> 00:51:58,365
-How did that fit in there?
-They're bigger on the inside.

641
00:51:58,449 --> 00:52:00,784
Roboforms are not necessary.

642
00:52:00,868 --> 00:52:04,330
My children may feast on Martian flesh.

643
00:52:04,413 --> 00:52:07,666
-Oh, but I'm not from Mars.
-Then where?

644
00:52:08,917 --> 00:52:12,504
My home planet is far away and long since gone.

645
00:52:13,005 --> 00:52:14,882
But its name lives on.

646
00:52:16,216 --> 00:52:17,509
Gallifrey.

647
00:52:19,053 --> 00:52:22,890
-They murdered the Racnoss.
-I warned you.

648
00:52:24,350 --> 00:52:25,768
You did this.

649
00:52:27,061 --> 00:52:29,605
No, no. Don't!

650
00:52:31,565 --> 00:52:33,150
No!

651
00:52:33,817 --> 00:52:38,906
No! No! No!

652
00:52:39,823 --> 00:52:41,033
No!

653
00:52:52,753 --> 00:52:54,380
No!

654
00:53:04,932 --> 00:53:06,934
No!

655
00:53:17,111 --> 00:53:18,862
No!

656
00:53:18,946 --> 00:53:22,116
My children!

657
00:53:25,994 --> 00:53:28,789
(EMPRESS SHRIEKING)

658
00:53:29,748 --> 00:53:33,043
My children!

659
00:53:39,967 --> 00:53:43,470
My children!

660
00:53:46,473 --> 00:53:47,766
Doctor!

661
00:53:48,851 --> 00:53:50,894
You can stop now.

662
00:53:50,978 --> 00:53:54,815
My children!

663
00:54:02,573 --> 00:54:04,616
Come on, time to find a way out.

664
00:54:15,169 --> 00:54:18,672
Transport me!

665
00:54:23,844 --> 00:54:27,848
Oh, they will suffer. So suffer!

666
00:54:28,307 --> 00:54:31,685
This planet shall be scorched.

667
00:54:33,353 --> 00:54:35,397
What about the Empress?

668
00:54:35,481 --> 00:54:38,734
She's used up all her Huon energy.
She's defenceless.

669
00:54:46,784 --> 00:54:49,453
MAN: Orders of Mr Saxon, fire at will.

670
00:54:49,536 --> 00:54:50,621
Fire!

671
00:55:03,801 --> 00:55:05,803
(SCREAMING)

672
00:55:34,540 --> 00:55:37,918
-There's just one problem.
-What is it?

673
00:55:39,920 --> 00:55:41,713
We've drained the Thames.

674
00:55:44,299 --> 00:55:46,426
(FOG HORNS BLOWING)

675
00:55:46,760 --> 00:55:49,096
(THE DOCTOR AND DONNA LAUGHING)

676
00:55:54,142 --> 00:55:57,688
DOCTOR: There we go.
I told you she'd be all right.

677
00:55:57,771 --> 00:56:00,482
-Survive anything.
-More than I've done.

678
00:56:05,070 --> 00:56:07,781
Well, all the Huon particles are gone.

679
00:56:08,574 --> 00:56:11,702
-No damage. You're fine.
-Yeah, apart from that.

680
00:56:13,120 --> 00:56:17,457
I missed my wedding, I lost my job
and became a widow on the same day.

681
00:56:17,541 --> 00:56:19,084
Sort of.

682
00:56:19,793 --> 00:56:21,587
I couldn't save him.

683
00:56:22,421 --> 00:56:23,714
He deserved it.

684
00:56:28,802 --> 00:56:30,679
No, he didn't.

685
00:56:33,223 --> 00:56:36,476
I better get inside, they'll be worried.

686
00:56:36,852 --> 00:56:39,271
Best Christmas present they could have.

687
00:56:40,147 --> 00:56:44,109
-Oh, no, I forgot, you hate Christmas.
-Yes, I do.

688
00:56:45,652 --> 00:56:48,530
Even if it's snowing?

689
00:57:00,876 --> 00:57:02,753
I can't believe you did that.

690
00:57:02,836 --> 00:57:05,923
Oh, basic atmospheric excitation.

691
00:57:11,970 --> 00:57:14,890
-Merry Christmas.
-And you.

692
00:57:21,146 --> 00:57:25,734
So, what will you do with yourself now?

693
00:57:26,985 --> 00:57:29,655
Not getting married, for starters.

694
00:57:29,738 --> 00:57:34,034
And I'm not gonna temp any more.
I don't know, travel.

695
00:57:34,868 --> 00:57:38,747
See a bit more of planet Earth, walk in the dust.

696
00:57:40,874 --> 00:57:44,419
Just go out there and do something.

697
00:57:47,673 --> 00:57:50,884
-Well, you could always...
-What?

698
00:57:53,387 --> 00:57:54,972
...come with me.

699
00:57:56,723 --> 00:57:58,892
-No.
-Okay.

700
00:57:59,393 --> 00:58:01,436
-I can't.
-No, that's fine.

701
00:58:02,145 --> 00:58:06,483
No, but really, I mean, everything we did today,

702
00:58:06,566 --> 00:58:08,819
do you live your life like that?

703
00:58:09,861 --> 00:58:11,613
Not all the time.

704
00:58:12,364 --> 00:58:13,657
I think you do.

705
00:58:16,326 --> 00:58:18,078
And I couldn't.

706
00:58:19,871 --> 00:58:21,832
But you've seen it out there.

707
00:58:22,708 --> 00:58:25,377
-It's beautiful.
-And it's terrible.

708
00:58:26,378 --> 00:58:30,090
That place was flooded and burning
and they were dying,

709
00:58:30,173 --> 00:58:35,595
and you stood there like,
I don't know, a stranger.

710
00:58:37,597 --> 00:58:40,892
And then you made it snow!
I mean, you scare me to death.

711
00:58:44,438 --> 00:58:45,981
Well, then.

712
00:58:49,443 --> 00:58:52,446
I'll tell you what I will do, though.
Christmas dinner.

713
00:58:53,864 --> 00:58:56,658
-Oh, come on.
-I don't do that sort of thing.

714
00:58:56,783 --> 00:58:58,702
You did it last year, you said so.

715
00:58:58,785 --> 00:59:02,289
And you might as well
because Mum always cooks enough for 20.

716
00:59:06,626 --> 00:59:11,965
All right then. But you go first,
better warn them, and don't say I'm a Martian.

717
00:59:13,216 --> 00:59:16,928
I just have to park her properly.
She might drift off to the Middle Ages.

718
00:59:17,012 --> 00:59:18,972
I'll see you in a minute.

719
00:59:21,808 --> 00:59:23,143
(WHOOSHING)

720
00:59:23,226 --> 00:59:24,603
Doctor!

721
00:59:25,020 --> 00:59:26,521
Doctor!

722
00:59:27,981 --> 00:59:29,941
Blimey, you can shout.

723
00:59:31,860 --> 00:59:35,405
-Am I ever gonna see you again?
-If I'm lucky.

724
00:59:38,158 --> 00:59:41,495
Just promise me one thing.

725
00:59:43,497 --> 00:59:45,207
Find someone.

726
00:59:46,500 --> 00:59:49,169
-I don't need anyone.
-Yes, you do.

727
00:59:50,587 --> 00:59:54,007
'Cause sometimes I think you need someone
to stop you.

728
00:59:56,593 --> 00:59:58,011
Yeah.

729
01:00:00,847 --> 01:00:03,100
Thanks then, Donna. Good luck.

730
01:00:04,059 --> 01:00:05,936
And just...

731
01:00:07,354 --> 01:00:09,397
be magnificent.

732
01:00:11,775 --> 01:00:13,944
I think I will, yeah.

733
01:00:17,781 --> 01:00:20,867
-Doctor?
-Oh, what is it now?

734
01:00:22,953 --> 01:00:26,456
That friend of yours, what was her name?

735
01:00:28,125 --> 01:00:30,043
Her name was Rose.

736
01:00:39,511 --> 01:00:41,638
(WHOOSHING)

737
01:00:56,194 --> 01:00:59,239
-I'm the Doctor.
-Me, too, if I can pass my exams.

738
01:00:59,364 --> 01:01:00,657
-What was your name?
-Martha.

739
01:01:00,740 --> 01:01:01,950
Martha Jones.

740
01:01:03,577 --> 01:01:05,203
Rose her name was.
Not that you're replacing her.

741
01:01:05,287 --> 01:01:06,496
Never said I was.

742
01:01:08,081 --> 01:01:10,667
Monsters! There are monsters.

743
01:01:10,750 --> 01:01:12,252
It's started.

744
01:01:19,926 --> 01:01:21,094
Let her go!

745
01:01:22,929 --> 01:01:24,389
The Globe Theatre.

746
01:01:25,265 --> 01:01:27,017
Mr Shakespeare, isn't it?

747
01:01:27,434 --> 01:01:30,020
What are you standing there for? Come on.

748
01:01:32,606 --> 01:01:34,816
Very well dressed for a hitchhiker.

749
01:01:40,697 --> 01:01:41,781
No!

750
01:01:48,413 --> 01:01:50,457
No!

751
01:01:50,540 --> 01:01:53,043
Tonight, I'm going to perform a miracle.

752
01:01:54,961 --> 01:01:56,713
I'm 76 years old.

